500|$|Armenia ( [...] , , tr. Hayastan, Armeniya), officially the Armenian Soviet Socialist Republic (Armenian SSR; [...] Armyanskaya Sovetskaya Sotsialističeskaya Respublika), also {{commonly}} referred to as Soviet <b>Armenia,</b> was one <b>of</b> <b>the</b> constituent <b>republics</b> <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Soviet Union in December 1922 located in the South Caucasus region of Eurasia. It was established in December 1920, when the Soviets took over control <b>of</b> <b>the</b> short-lived First <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> <b>Armenia</b> and lasted until 1991. It is sometimes called <b>the</b> Second <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> <b>Armenia,</b> following <b>the</b> First <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> <b>Armenia's</b> demise.|$|R
