50|$|The Treaty of Batum {{was signed}} in Batum on June 4, 1918, between the Ottoman Empire and the three Transcaucasian states: <b>the</b> First <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> <b>Armenia,</b> <b>the</b> Azerbaijan Democratic <b>Republic</b> and <b>the</b> Democratic <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> Georgia. It was the first treaty <b>of</b> <b>the</b> First <b>Republic</b> <b>of</b> <b>Armenia</b> and <b>the</b> Azerbaijan Democratic <b>Republic</b> and had 14 articles.|$|R
